		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">Copy.</p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
				<p>At a meeting of the Congregation Keneseth<lb/> Israel&#44; held <date>April 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1854</date>&#44; at the<lb/> Committee rooms&#44; in <placeName>New Market<lb/> Street&#44; above Noble</placeName>&#44; the following pre&#45;<lb/>amble and resolutions were proposed<lb/> and unanimously adopted&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Whereas&#44; On the occasion of the<lb/> consecration of our new Synagogue we<lb/> have derived such great benefit from various Gentlemen&#44; on whose kindness<lb/> and assistance we had no other claim<lb/> than that of charity&#44; that we deem it<lb/> expedient and proper to express our<lb/> thanks to them in this manner.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Be it therefore. Resolved. That<lb/> the thanks of the congregation are<lb/> due&#44; to the <persName>Rev. Isaac Leeser</persName>&#44; for<lb/> the excellent sermon which he delivered<lb/> on the occasion&#44; to the <persName>Rev. Fraenkel</persName>&#44;<lb/> <persName>Rev. S. Morais</persName>&#44; <persName>Rev. Pope</persName> and <persName>Rev.<lb/> Fassbender</persName> for the services they so</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>kindly volunteered and so ably performed&#59;<lb/> and also to the <persName>Rev. L. Naumburg</persName><lb/> for the exertions he used in rendering<lb/> the ceremonies worthy of the praise<lb/> and admiration of those who<lb/> participated in them.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Resolved. That we tender our<lb/> sincere thanks to the Presidents<lb/> and Committees of the Congregations<lb/> &#8222;Beth Elohim&#8221; &#8222;Beth Israel&#8221;<lb/> and &#8222;Rodef Sholom&#8221; for the favors<lb/> which they accorded with such good<lb/> will and at so short a notice&#59; and<lb/> also to <persName>Messrs. Jacob Langsdorf</persName>&#44;<lb/> <persName>Josep Einstein</persName>&#44; <persName>Allen</persName>&#44; <persName>Henry<lb/> Mayer</persName>&#44; <persName>M. Goldsmith</persName>&#44; <persName>Jacob<lb/> Mayer</persName> and other gentlemen who<lb/> aided in the management.  Also<lb/> to <persName>Professors Fisher</persName> and <persName>Sherrer</persName><lb/> for the skillful manner in which<lb/> they conducted the musical arrange<lb/>ments&#59; to the ladies and gentlemen of the<lb/> choir and to <persName>Messrs. Shoemaker &#38; Co.</persName> for their</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>kind loan of a melodeon&#44; and to all others<lb/> who&#44; though&#44; their names may not be<lb/> mentioned here&#44; have assisted in the cere&#45;<lb/>monies.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Resolved. That a copy of these<lb/> resolutions be sent to each of the reverend<lb/> gentlemen and others herein mentioned&#44;<lb/> and that they be inserted for publication<lb/> in the Ledger&#44; Daily Register&#44; Freie<lb/> Heimath and Democrat.</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Weidnitzer</persName>&#44; Secr.</p>
			
